-- South African Competitiveness Harmed by Cash Inflows,Pravin Gordhan Says
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-10-28T18:16:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/south-african-competitiveness-harmed-by-cash-inflows-pravin-gordhan-says.html
South Africa’s competitiveness as an
economy is being harmed by inflows of funds into bonds and
stocks, which are strengthening the rand, Pravin Gordhan, the
country’s finance minister, said in an address to academics in
Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Johannesburg at 
